South African National Parks (SANParks) announced on Wednesday that the Lions Head summit situated within the Table Mountain National Park (TMNP) has reopened on 9th of September 2020 after it was closed in June due to non-compliance with Lockdown Level 3 regulations. The reopening comes after The Table Mountain Aerial Cableway Company (TMACC) opened at the beginning of the month. The following protocols have been put in place: “We encourage all users to adhere to the regulations imposed by the NCCC and SANParks to avoid possible re-closure of the iconic summit.” – SANPARKS